329
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:10,080
In your scheme from clip flyback converter with stabilized output voltage and current protection.

330
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:20,480
At drain of FET transistor stands diode FR207, resistance 5.1 Ohm and capacitor 1 nF 1000 V.

331
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:30,880
If I correctly understand work of this trio, then these elements needed for restraining energy surge from coil at moment of transistor turn off.

332
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:42,660
Role of capacitor — absorb this surge, resistor — prepare capacitor to absorb next surge of diode, not let high potential back to drain.

333
00:36:43,180 --> 00:36:46,260
Did error not creep in arrangement of these elements?

334
00:36:47,940 --> 00:36:51,000
Now examine this scheme more detail.

335
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:56,200
Speech goes about this scheme and this trio.

336
00:36:57,860 --> 00:37:02,020
Capacitor, diode FR207 and resistance.

337
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:09,580
Here earlier in video clip you saw 5.1 Ohm, now I here use 22 Ohm.

338
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:12,160
Here can vary this resistance.

339
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:17,280
No error in arrangement of details here, this done by me consciously.

340
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:22,380
And I watched oscillograms of key work and what here happens.

341
00:37:23,460 --> 00:37:35,660
Most often accustomed to see such schemes when diode at drain of FET key and connects directly to capacitor.

342
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:40,620
And parallel to capacitor is resistance.

343
00:37:41,620 --> 00:37:43,800
Here system works so.

344
00:37:43,900 --> 00:37:53,100
When happens key closure, forms surge that cut off by capacity charge of this capacitor.

345
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:56,840
Surge goes through diode FR207.

346
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:08,480
See that with one plate capacitor connected to plus power and accordingly to one of leads of primary winding 9 turns.

347
00:38:10,620 --> 00:38:13,900
So to it applied amplitude of this surge.

348
00:38:14,820 --> 00:38:21,400
When surge amplitude reached maximum, then capacitor at us charges to this amplitude.

349
00:38:21,520 --> 00:38:23,100
Further happens its fall.

350
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:31,960
And capacitor starts discharging through current-limiting resistance 22 Ohm on primary winding.

351
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:41,040
Thereby increasing time of this surge that forms at us at key drain.

352
00:38:41,420 --> 00:38:42,880
No error in this.

353
00:38:42,980 --> 00:38:45,600
You can self check, assembling this scheme.

354
00:38:46,220 --> 00:38:50,420
Can naturally change location of details by your discretion.

355
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:58,740
I consider this optimal scheme solution for low-voltage power of flyback converter.

